info.name: [Fulfillment Inbound API v2024] Small Parcel Delivery (SPD) with Non-Partnered Carrier (nPCP)
info.description: ### Overview This Selling Partner APIs (SP API) collection shows end-to-end Send To Amazon workflow for **Small Parcel Delivery** **(SPD) Inbound Shipments with Non-Partnered Carrier (your own transportation carrier)** using the new Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA) Inbound v2024 API operations. This collection supports below operations, - Access token retrieval. - Complete FBA Inbound API requests, including all required parameters, for creating, managing, and sending inbound shipments using individual boxes through your own transportation carrier. - Print FBA labels. ### Steps 1. Variables tab has all the required variables for the API operations. Modify them with your actual values. 2. Call the _**Authorization API**_ to get the _**access token**_ in exchange to the refresh token. This access token is passed as a header to all the SP API calls. 3. Call the _**createInboundPlan**_ operation with attributes defined in the postman request. 4. Next proceed to _**follow the order of the operations mentioned in the collection**_ to _**pack the items**_ using packing API operations , choose _**where and how to send**_ using placement and transportation API operations as well as print the required _**labels**_. 5. To choose a _**Small Parcel Delivery**_ with your _**own transportation carrier**_, from the _**listTransportationOptions**_ operation choose the _**transportationOptionId**_ with _**shippingMode**_ _as_ one of the [small parcel options](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/fulfillment-inbound-api-v2024-03-20-reference#shippingconfiguration) _and_ one of the suitable carrier with _**shippingSolution**_ _as_ _**USE_YOUR_OWN_CARRIER.**_ _You also need to provide a delivery window using the_ _**delivery window API**_ _operations._ 6. After each _**post operation**_, you need to check the status for success and issues using the _**inboundOperationStatus**_ API call by passing the _**operationId**_. You can cancel the inbound plan created through this workflow for test using the _**cancelInboundPlan**_ _operation._

request.description:
- **client_id and client_secret -** You get these credentials after you register your application. Refer to [Viewing your application information and credentials](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/viewing-your-application-information-and-credentials) for more information.
    
- **refresh_token -** You get your LWA refresh token from Seller Central after [authorizing your application.](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/authorizing-selling-partner-api-applications)

item.name: Cancel Inbound Plan

request.description:

item.description:
Use this operation to cancel the create Inbound shipment plan.

Charges may apply if the cancellation is performed outside of a void window. The window for Amazon Partnered Carriers is _**24 hours for Small Parcel Delivery (SPD)**_ and _**one hour for Less-Than-Truckload (LTL)**_ carrier shipments.
